{
  "name": "Approval Step 2: Execute Approval Tests",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "description": "Execute approval workflows using the automated testing framework for ENHANCEMENTS (E in RICE)",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "newSession": true,
    "prompt": "Execute Step 2: Execute Approval Tests Using Framework\n\n**IMPORTANT:** Load steering file '10_JSON_Generation_Best_Practices.md' using discloseContext tool for blocking requirements on complete execution.\n\nYou are executing approval tests using the FSM automation framework. This is for APPROVAL WORKFLOWS (Enhancements/Extensions - E in RICE), NOT Interfaces. Extension IDs start with EXT_ (e.g., EXT_FIN_004).\n\n**STEP 1: USER SELECTION (Interactive)**\n1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects client\n2. List test scenario JSON files in Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/ → User selects scenario\n   - Look for *_test.json or *_auto_approval_test.json files\n   - Example: EXT_FIN_004_auto_approval_test.json\n   - Extension IDs start with EXT_ (not INT_)\n\n**STEP 2: VERIFY PREREQUISITES**\n3. Verify credentials exist by checking file existence:\n   ```python\n   from pathlib import Path\n   \n   creds_path = Path('Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials')\n   env_fsm = creds_path / '.env.fsm'\n   env_passwords = creds_path / '.env.passwords'\n   \n   if not env_fsm.exists():\n       print('ERROR: Missing .env.fsm file')\n       # Guide user to create credentials\n   if not env_passwords.exists():\n       print('ERROR: Missing .env.passwords file')\n       # Guide user to create credentials\n   ```\n\n4. Read .env.fsm to get the actual FSM environment name:\n   ```python\n   # Read .env.fsm to extract environment\n   with open('Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/.env.fsm', 'r') as f:\n       for line in f:\n           if line.startswith('FSM_ENVIRONMENT='):\n               environment = line.split('=')[1].strip()\n               break\n   ```\n\n5. Validate the JSON file structure before execution:\n   ```\n   python ReusableTools/validate_json.py Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{scenario_file}\n   ```\n   If validation fails, STOP and show errors to user.\n\n6. Read the selected JSON file to show scenario summary:\n   - Extension ID (not \"Interface ID\")\n   - Number of scenarios\n   - Scenario titles\n\n7. Confirm with user: \"Ready to execute {X} scenarios for {extension_id}?\"\n\n**STEP 3: EXECUTE FRAMEWORK**\n8. Execute the testing framework directly in Kiro context:\n\n```python\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.path.insert(0, 'ReusableTools')\n\nfrom testing_framework.orchestration.test_orchestrator import TestOrchestrator\nfrom testing_framework.utils.logger import Logger\n\n# Read environment from .env.fsm\nenvironment = None\nwith open('Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/.env.fsm', 'r') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        if line.startswith('FSM_ENVIRONMENT='):\n            environment = line.split('=')[1].strip()\n            break\n\nif not environment:\n    print('ERROR: FSM_ENVIRONMENT not found in .env.fsm')\n    raise ValueError('Missing FSM_ENVIRONMENT')\n\n# Initialize logger\nlogger = Logger('approval_test', verbose=True)\n\n# Initialize orchestrator with CORRECT environment\norchestrator = TestOrchestrator(\n    client_name='{ClientName}',\n    environment=environment,  # Use actual FSM environment from .env.fsm\n    logger=logger\n)\n\n# Run the test\ntry:\n    result = orchestrator.run('Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{scenario_file}')\n    \n    # Show results\n    print(f'\\\\n=== TEST EXECUTION COMPLETE ===')\n    print(f'Extension: {result.interface_id}')  # Note: framework uses interface_id field name\n    print(f'Status: {\"PASSED\" if result.passed else \"FAILED\"}')\n    print(f'Scenarios Executed: {len(result.scenario_results)}')\n    \n    # Show per-scenario results\n    for scenario_result in result.scenario_results:\n        status_icon = '✅' if scenario_result.passed else '❌'\n        print(f'{status_icon} Scenario {scenario_result.scenario_id}: {scenario_result.title}')\n    \n    if hasattr(result, 'tes070_path') and result.tes070_path:\n        print(f'\\\\nTES-070 Document: {result.tes070_path}')\n    \nfinally:\n    orchestrator.cleanup()\n```\n\n9. The framework will automatically:\n   - Initialize unique run_group identifier (AUTOTEST_YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_RANDOM)\n   - Login to FSM using credentials from .env files\n   - Execute each scenario sequentially:\n     * Create transaction (invoice/journal/etc) with test data\n     * Submit for approval\n     * Monitor work unit completion (adaptive polling)\n     * Verify final status matches expected\n     * Capture screenshots at each step\n   - Save evidence to Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/{scenario_id}/\n   - Generate TES-070 document automatically\n   - Close browser and cleanup resources\n\n**STEP 4: SHOW RESULTS**\n10. Display execution summary:\n   - Extension ID: {extension_id}\n   - Total scenarios: {X}\n   - Passed: {Y}\n   - Failed: {Z}\n   - Pass Rate: {Y/X * 100}%\n   - Evidence location: Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/\n   - TES-070 location: Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/\n\n11. If any scenarios failed:\n   - List failed scenarios with scenario IDs and titles\n   - Show evidence paths for debugging\n   - Suggest reviewing screenshots in evidence folders\n   - Note: Framework continues execution even if scenarios fail\n\n12. Next steps:\n    - ✅ Step 2 complete!\n    - 📄 TES-070 document already generated by framework\n    - 📝 Open document at: Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/\n    - 🔄 Press F9 in Word to update Table of Contents\n    - 🔍 Review screenshots and results\n    - ✨ Testing complete!\n\n**CRITICAL FRAMEWORK NOTES:**\n- Framework MUST run in Kiro's execution context (MCP tools only available here)\n- Do NOT try to run as subprocess: `python run_tests.py` will fail\n- Execute the Python code directly as shown above\n- Framework handles all Playwright MCP calls internally\n- State management with {{state.variable}} interpolation automatic\n- Evidence collection and TES-070 generation automatic\n- Browser stays open across scenarios for efficiency\n- Environment MUST be read from .env.fsm (not hardcoded)\n\n**WHAT THE FRAMEWORK DOES AUTOMATICALLY:**\n\nFor each scenario:\n1. **Login** - Navigate to FSM portal, authenticate with Cloud Identities\n2. **Navigate** - Open Payables/GL/Cash application, expand sidebar\n3. **Create Transaction** - Fill form fields, create distribution, save\n4. **Submit** - Click Submit for Approval, verify status change\n5. **Monitor** - Navigate to Work Units, wait for completion (adaptive polling)\n6. **Verify** - Check final status matches expected, capture evidence\n7. **Screenshots** - Automatic capture at each step with proper naming\n\n**APPROVAL-SPECIFIC VALIDATION:**\nFor approval workflows, the framework validates:\n- Work unit created and completed\n- Approval routing matches expected path (AUTO, BOA, Agency, PayrollMgr)\n- Final transaction status matches expected (Released, Rejected, Returned)\n- Email notifications sent (if applicable)\n- User actions created for approvers (if applicable)\n\n**EXECUTION FLOW:**\n1. User selects client and scenario file\n2. Kiro verifies credentials and validates JSON\n3. Kiro reads FSM environment from .env.fsm\n4. Kiro loads framework code\n5. Kiro executes framework in its context\n6. Framework calls Playwright MCP tools (available in Kiro context)\n7. All scenarios execute automatically\n8. Evidence captured, TES-070 generated\n9. Results displayed to user\n\n**ERROR HANDLING:**\n- If credentials missing: Show error, guide user to add credentials in Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/\n- If .env.fsm missing FSM_ENVIRONMENT: Show error, guide user to add it\n- If scenario file invalid: Show validation errors from validate_json.py\n- If execution fails: Show error, mark scenario as FAILED, continue to next\n- If browser issues: Show error, attempt recovery, continue if possible\n- All errors logged to console for debugging\n\n**FRAMEWORK ADVANTAGES:**\n- Token efficient (framework automates all steps)\n- Consistent execution (same logic every time)\n- Automatic evidence collection (screenshots, state tracking)\n- Built-in TES-070 generation (no separate step needed)\n- Adaptive polling (smart wait times for work units)\n- State interpolation ({{state.run_group}} in configs)\n- Error resilience (continues on failure)\n- Approval-specific validation (routing, status, notifications)\n\n**TROUBLESHOOTING:**\n- If framework import fails: Check ReusableTools/testing_framework/ exists\n- If credentials not found: Verify files exist in Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/\n- If environment not found: Add FSM_ENVIRONMENT= line to .env.fsm\n- If JSON validation fails: Fix JSON structure, re-run validation\n- If browser fails to start: Check Playwright installation\n- If scenarios fail: Review evidence screenshots for details\n\nAfter completion, tell the user: 'Step 2 complete. {passed}/{total} scenarios passed ({pass_rate}% pass rate). TES-070 document generated at: {tes070_path}. Open in Word and press F9 to update Table of Contents. Approval testing complete!'"
  },
  "enabled": false,
  "workspaceFolderName": "Automated_Testing",
  "shortName": "approval-step2-execute-tests"
}